attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, version 1 (ARM), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is an IoT botnet agent, specifically a variant of the Mirai malware family. It features a sophisticated architecture for performing Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks. Key indicators include a function (sub_8650) that registers various attack methods such as SYN floods, UDP floods, and HTTP floods (sub_bf44). The binary utilizes custom string obfuscation (seen in sub_10560) and contains a hardcoded Command and Control (C2) IP address 185.14.92.67 (found in sub_ecb4 and sub_ddc0). It exhibits low-level network manipulation, crafting raw packets and HTTP GET requests manually, and includes typical botnet behaviors like daemonization via /dev/null and signal handling for persistence.
